        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "Passing a Course",
          "Pass (0) vs Fail (1)",
          "866 students in Thessaloniki",
          "3 courses: Physics III, Phjysical Chemistry I & Analtical Chemistry Labs",
          "LMS logs, Intermediate and Final Grades",
          "[Number of Views per module]",
          "End of Course",
          "Features are extracted from the logs themselves using a plugin.\n\nThese are subsequently given to a set of fuzzy learning algorithms.\n\nAt the second stage authors 4 distinc strategies:\n\nUncertainty Sample with LC, Hinted SVM, QUIRE and Random Sampling.",
          "FMARR, MFPC AIWA/OWA, FPC GA/LGA, PT, PTTD, FPC OWA, Naive Bayesm IBk-5NN, Random Forest, GBoost",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{Friedman Aligned Rank Accuracy: 11.2 - PT,  Friedman Aligned Rank AUC: 15 - PTTD, Friedman Aligned Rank AUC: 15.1 - PTTD}",
          "Authors use AutoML to do hyper.-parameter tuning od different fuzzy learning algorithms to predict a student’s ability to pass our fail a course.\n\nEven after comparison using Standard ML algorithms, the rank performance of the Fuzzy Classifiers beats the remaining models.\n\nTests using the different forms of resampling show that Hinted SVM or QUIRE are decent techniques.\n\n",
          "No consideration of adding other data sources.\n\nNo explanation of learning using resources not available in the LMS.\n\nUncreative feature engineering and extraction."
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
